{
  "doc_id": "16383",
  "text": "A number of methods for mining the Web have been applied in the last two decades including crawling, indexing and modeling the data using unsupervised, semi-supervised and supervised machine learning methods as well as, using social network analysis [CITATION_1] . There are several areas in the web mining community [CITATION_2] where content and access logs were used to profile users. There, the authors mostly focus on the application of profiling to recommender systems and e-commerce based on query logs. This paper focuses on user modeling for large web sites providing content, such as magazines or newspapers, with the task of classifying users into pre-defined demographic segments.",
